  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building Resilience to Enhance Adaptable Development in Somaliland (BREADS)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Pastoralist communities</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Building Resilience to Enhance Adaptable Development in Somaliland (BREADS) project aims to enhance community livelihood coping strategies to recurrent drought for men, women, and children in pastoral communities. The targeted area has been experiencing food insecurity due to recurrent drought brought by climate change coupled with limited livelihood options by the rural pastoral communities. To address this, World Concern will conduct trainings on disaster risk response and natural resource management, strengthen and support farming activities, and establish microfinance infrastructure for savings and loans. World Concern will also assist pastoralist communities in Eastern Somaliland to increase their resilience to drought and other natural hazards connected to climate change.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Train and perform best practices, remote monitoring, inter-faith and cross cultural issues.
Community meetings.
Capacity Building.
Train on Disaster Risk Reduction.
Form farming groups.
Distribute tree seedlings to students.
Train farming groups.
Distribute seeds and introduce alternative crops.
Demonstration plots.
Develop self-help groups.</narrative>
  </description>
